        {
          "username": "Inspired",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "100529500353516865254",
          "user_review_count": 134,
          "user_photo_count": 415,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGckXcNuGGjm01CxJQhHywu7eiSDJ7ah2yGkWosf7F-L82vw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "This clinic may work great for people with Medicaid or other subsidized health insurances but I would avoid this place at all cost as a PPO insurance holder. First of all, they prescribed so much blood work that I literally fainted during the draw. This is just as a part of the annual routine checkup. Next, when I called them to inquire about my test results, they hung up on me. When I called to resend my prescription to the pharmacy, they hung up on me. The staff is very unprofessional, and it seems like everyone has an attitude present at city-sponsored hospitals. I felt like they absolutely do not care about my health, well-being, or comfort. They will bill your insurance  but won't give any answers or follow up.\n\nUpdate: 6 month after my checkup visit I received a bill for the balance that my insurance did not cover (it should have covered my annual check up but this is a different story). My name on the bill is misspelled, and the phone line that is responsible for handling bill questions is not working. I will definitely stay away from this sloppy nightmare in the future.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUM3M0tpdmJ3EAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x2b7a4533c78299b1!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIC73Kivbw%7C%7C?hl=en",
